						<div class="postbody">Nice doc!
<br />What about the following: for those of us that will use a generic runtime made in assembler but will code our games in c, thus not being able to write custom NMI routines, would it be fine just updating a zeropage var in NMI which means the start of vblank by being non-zero, and then wait for this to happen in the main thread, do graphics, and then set that var to zero?</div>

